│ The issue lies in the `AShrChecker` lambda function, where the code attempts to cast a `Value` to an `Instruction` without verifying its type. This can lead to an assertion failure when the `Value` is not an   │
│ `Instruction`, such as when it is a `poison` value.                                                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ To fix this, we need to add a type check before performing the cast. If the `Value` is not an `Instruction`, we should skip processing it.                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ### Proposed Fix                                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ Modify the `AShrChecker` lambda function to include a check for the type of `Value`. If the `Value` is not an `Instruction`, we will return `false` for that specific `Value`.                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ### Code Change                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ auto AShrChecker = [&](unsigned BitWidth, unsigned OrigBitWidth) {                                                                                                                                                │
│   return all_of(E.Scalars, [&](Value *V) {                                                                                                                                                                        │
│     if (!isa<Instruction>(V)) // Ensure V is an Instruction                                                                                                                                                       │
│       return false; // Skip processing if V is not an Instruction                                                                                                                                                 │
│     auto *I = cast<Instruction>(V);                                                                                                                                                                               │
│     KnownBits AmtKnownBits = computeKnownBits(I->getOperand(1), *DL);                                                                                                                                             │
│     unsigned ShiftedBits = OrigBitWidth - BitWidth;                                                                                                                                                               │
│     return AmtKnownBits.getMaxValue().ult(BitWidth) &&                                                                                                                                                            │
│            ShiftedBits < ComputeNumSignBits(I->getOperand(0), *DL, 0, AC,                                                                                                                                         │
│                                             nullptr, DT);                                                                                                                                                         │
│   });                                                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ };                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ This change ensures that the code does not attempt to cast non-`Instruction` values, preventing the assertion failure.                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ I will now apply this fix to the code.                                                                                                                                                                            │
